pageContext.claim: “Even look at the first quarter, we're at 3.2 percent. Nobody expected that. They thought it would be one -- you know, the first quarter is always very low. We're at 3.2 percent.”
pageContext.analysis: Nope. Looking at the last 30 years of GDP data, the first quarter often was among the strongest. The U.S. last had first-quarter GDP growth above 3 percent in 2015.
